    "summary": "I hold a master's degree in Environment and Development from the University of Edinburgh, where I focused on the intersection of environmental and social issues. I was formally a research assistant at the Research Center of Environmental Changes and Biodiversity Research Center at Academia Sinica, Taiwan's leading research institute. My core competencies include data analysis, project design, and interviewing.\n\nIn my previous role as a green energy planner at Corporate Synergy Development Center, I executed and managed green grants on local green industrial research and development for the Energy Bureau, Ministry of Economic Affairs of Taiwan. I also conducted ESG and Net Zero research on international policy and best practices. As a volunteer, I searched and applied for grants on reforestation and poverty alleviation for a cooperated NGO in Haiti with Greenstand, a global platform that empowers people to restore ecosystems.\n\nI am passionate about creating positive environmental and social impact through research and collaboration. I can bring diverse perspectives and experiences to the team, as I have lived, studied, and worked in different countries and cultures. I am fluent in Chinese, English, and French.",
